# Never copy host node_modules into build contexts — images install fresh.
# A Windows host node_modules can shadow the in-image install and corrupt the
# build (e.g. a partial/truncated typescript binary). Every service Dockerfile
# runs its own npm install, so host node_modules are never needed.
**/node_modules
**/.git

# Large dirs irrelevant to any image build — keep the build context small (a
# repo-root context otherwise pulls these in, e.g. for the frontend image which
# now builds from `context: .`). Worktrees alone are >1GB.
.claude
FuzeInfra
fuzefront-website
.remember
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
*.log
**/*.tsbuildinfo
